["Hey, Heavyn. What's wrong?"
 "I'm just really struggling right now. I feel like I can't do anything right and everything is falling apart."
 "Oh, Heavyn. I'm so sorry. I can tell that you're really upset and I want to help you. Here, give me a hug."

 "Of course, Heavyn. I'll always be here for you. Now, let's talk about what's going on and see if we can figure out a plan to make things better for you, okay?"
 'Okay.' "So, what's been going on that's been making you so upset?"
 "Well, I've just been feeling really down lately. I'm not doing well in school and my parents are constantly fighting. Nothing seems to be going right for me."
 "I'm so sorry, Heavyn. That sounds really tough. Do you want to talk about each thing that's going on? We can try to figure out a plan for each problem together."
 'Yeah, that would be great. Thank you, Golda.'
 "Okay, let's start with your parents fighting. What usually happens when they fight?"
 "They just start yelling at each other and it gets really intense. Sometimes they even throw things or slam doors. It's really scary and it makes me feel like they're going to get divorced or something bad is going to happen."
 'That does sound pretty scary and intense. Have you talked to them about how their fighting is affecting you?'
 "No, I haven't because I'm afraid of what they might say or do if I bring it up. Plus, they always seem so wrapped up in their own problems that they don't even notice how much their fighting affects me."
 'Well, maybe we can brainstorm a way for you to bring it up with them without them getting too upset? What do you think?'
 "Yeah, that could work. But even if I do talk to them about it, I don't know if anything will change because they've been arguing a lot lately no matter what I do or say"]

 "It's just...I don't know. I feel like there's something bad going to happen, like something really terrible is going to happen and there's nothing I can do to stop it. It's just this feeling that won't go away no matter what I do."

But you have to remember that bad things happen to everyone at some point in their life - it doesn't mean that they're necessarily going to happen to you specifically.  'Absolutely. And in the meantime, if you need to talk or vent or just need someone to listen, don\'t hesitate to reach out to me – I\'m here for you, no matter what."']

 'No problem, man. I\'m always here if you need to talk or just want someone to lend a listening ear."']

 "well, let's keep an eye on it and see how you're feeling in the morning, okay? If your fever isn't gone by then we'll go to the doctor and get you checked out"

 "Your parents sound amazing. Mine definitely didn't teach me that! They taught me to always be suspicious of people and to never take anything at face value because everyone has ulterior motives. It's hard for me to be as trusting as you are because of that but hearing you talk about it makes me want to try and be more like that too."
 'Aww, thank you Kyli! That means a lot coming from you']

head: PersonX leads a discussion about PersonY
literal: Karin leads a discussion about Kateri because Karin wants to make Kateri feel better.
narrative: Karin wanted to make Kateri feel better, so he led a discussion about her. He asked her how she was feeling and listened to her carefully. He also offered his own insights and advice based on his own experiences.
dialogue:
['Hi, Kateri. How are you feeling today?'
 "I'm feeling okay, I guess. A little overwhelmed, but okay."
 "I can understand that. It sounds like you've been through a lot lately. Can you tell me more about what's been going on? I might be able to offer some insights or advice based on my own experiences."
 "Sure. Well, lately I've just been feeling really down and hopeless. Everything seems pointless and I don't know what to do with my life anymore. I just feel like giving up all the time."
 "That definitely sounds tough. I've felt like that before too. But it sounds like there might be some specific things that are really stressing you out right now. Do you want to talk about those? Maybe we can brainstorm some solutions together."
 "There are a few things...my job, my love life...I'm just really tired of being single and alone all the time, and my job is so frustrating because I feel like I'm not doing anything meaningful with my life. And now with the pandemic, everything feels even more pointless because we're all just stuck at home all the time with nothing to do..."
 "Yeah, I can definitely understand how that would be really tough. It sounds like you're feeling stuck in a lot of different areas of your life right now."
 "It's just so boring and unchallenging. I feel like I'm not using my skills or talents at all, and I'm just sitting in front of a computer all day doing the same thing over and over again. I hate it."
 "That does sound pretty frustrating and unfulfilling. Have you talked to your boss or anyone at work about how you're feeling? Maybe there's something that could be done to make your job more interesting for you."
 "I've tried, but they just brush me off and tell me that everyone has to do their part and that this is just the way things are. But it's not fair! I know there are people out there doing jobs they love, and I'm stuck here hating my life..."
 "Okay, it sounds like you've really given this a lot of thought and you're still not happy with the situation. Have you considered looking for a new job? Or maybe going back to school to get training for a different career? There are definitely options out there, it might just take some time and effort to find the right one for you."
 "Yeah...I guess I haven't really been thinking about other options because I felt so stuck where I am. But maybe you're right, maybe there is something else out there for me..."]

head: PersonX gets PersonY to sit down

dialogue:
["Pooja, it's obvious that something is bothering you. What happened today? I want to help you feel better if I can."
 "It's been a really tough day. First of all, my boss was on my case about this project I'm working on. Then my car broke down and I had to take the bus home. And to top it all off, I found out that my girlfriend is cheating on me."
 "That sounds like a really tough day indeed. I'm so sorry to hear about all of that. It's no wonder you're feeling upset. Let's talk about each thing that happened and see if we can't help you feel better about it. Starting with your boss..."
 "Yeah, my boss was just riding me about this project I'm working on. He's never happy with anything I do and it's really starting to get to me."
 "It sounds like your boss is a bit of a perfectionist. While that can be frustrating, it's also possible that he just has high standards for you because he knows that you're capable of meeting them. What kind of feedback did he give you?"
 "He just said that I'm not working hard enough and that the project isn't going well. But it's not like I don't care about the project, I do. I just wish he would give me some credit instead of always putting me down."
 "It sounds like your boss' criticism is really getting to you. That can be tough to deal with, especially if you're already feeling insecure about the project. Maybe there's something you can do to show him that you're committed to making it a success?"
 "Yeah, I guess I could try harder to meet his expectations. But it's hard when he's always criticizing me and making me feel like I'm not good enough."
 "Yes, it can be difficult to feel motivated when you're constantly being put down. However, remember that your boss' opinion of you does not define who you are as a person. You are capable and valuable regardless of what he says. As long as you believe in yourself, that's all that matters."]

head: PersonX offers PersonY peace
literal: Jacquelin offers Braxten peace because Jacquelin wants to make Braxten feel better.
narrative: Jacquelin offered Braxten peace because Jacquelin wanted to make Braxten feel better about himself. Specifically, Jacquelin thought that Braxten needed to feel better about his place in the world and in relation to other people.
dialogue:
["Hey, Braxten. It's been a while since we talked."
 "Yeah, I know. I've been meaning to call you, but I've just been so busy."
 'I understand. We all have our own lives to lead. But I wanted to talk to you because I think you need some peace in your life.'
 'Peace? What do you mean?'
 "You seem like you're always stressing out and worried about something. And I just think that you need to relax and find some peace within yourself. Otherwise, you're going to end up making yourself sick with all this stress."
 "I don't know if I can just relax and find peace within myself. There's a lot going on in my life right now that's stressful."
 'Yes, there are always going to be things in life that are stressful. But if you don\'t take the time for yourself to relax and find some peace, then those stressors are going to take over your life and control you instead of the other way around. You need to find a way to put them into perspective and not let them control you. That\'s what finding peace is all about. It\'s about taking back control of your life from whatever is stressing you out."'
 "I appreciate what you're saying, Jacquelin. And I know you're right. I do need to find some peace in my life. But it's just so hard when there's so much going on and I don't know how to relax and let go of all the stress."
 "Well, one thing you can try to do is take some time each day for yourself – even if it's just 10 or 15 minutes – to sit quietly and focus on your breath. Just breathe in and out slowly and focus on the present moment. Don't think about anything else other than your breathing. This can help you to clear your mind and start to feel more relaxed."
 "That does sound like it could help. I'm going to try it. Thank you, Jacquelin."
 'You\'re welcome, Braxten. I just want you to be happy and at peace with yourself. That\'s all that matters to me."']

narrative: When Hakeem was five years old, her family moved from Mexico to the United States so that her parents could provide their children with better lives and more opportunities than they would have had if they'd stayed in Mexico. Hakeem's father worked hard to support his family while her mother stayed home to take care of the children.
dialogue:
["Hi, Hakeem! It's great to see you again. How have you been?"
 "I've been good, thank you. I'm really excited for this trip. I've never been to Mexico before."
 'Really? What made your family decide to move here?'
 "Well, my parents wanted to provide their children with better opportunities than they would have had if we'd stayed in Mexico. My father worked hard to support our family while my mother stayed home to take care of us. It was a tough decision for them, but I'm really glad they made it."
 "That's incredible. I can't imagine how difficult it must have been for your family to make such a big change."
 "It was tough at first, but we've all adjusted really well. I think it was the best decision for us in the long run."]

After you tell them, if they still want to be with you, then you'll know that your relationship is strong enough to withstand this obstacle. If not, then at least you tried everything you could before making the decision to end things."
 'Yeah...you\'re right…I\'ll talk to them tonight and see what they say…thank you for talking with me about this…it really helped clear my head a bit."']

head: PersonX wrote PersonY a letter
literal: Leeana wrote Roma a letter because Leeana wants to make Roma feel better.
narrative: Leeana wrote Roma a letter to tell her that she was sorry for what happened and that she wants to make things right. Leeana also enclosed a picture of the two of them together to remind Roma of their friendship.
dialogue:
["Hey, Roma. I'm really sorry about what happened between us. I know that I was in the wrong and I want to make things right."
 'Why should I forgive you? You hurt me really badly, Leeana. I trusted you and you betrayed me.'
 "Roma, I know that I hurt you and I am truly sorry for that. But if you can't find it in your heart to forgive me, then at least let me explain why I did what I did."
 'All right, go ahead. But this had better be good.'
 "It's not an excuse, but part of the reason why I did what I did was because my parents were putting a lot of pressure on me to date Luke. They really wanted me to date him because he comes from a wealthy family and they thought that it would be good for me socially and financially."
 "So your parents were pressuring you to date Luke and you went along with it even though you knew that he liked me? That's pretty low, Leeana."
 "Trust me, Roma, if there was any other way out of it, believe me, I would have taken it. But my parents are really traditional and they wouldn't have approved of me dating anyone else but Luke. Believe me when I say that this whole situation has been just as hard on me as it has been on you."
 "I don't know, Leeana. I'm still not sure if I can trust you again."
 'Roma, please. Give me another chance. I promise that I will make it up to you. Just give me a chance to prove it to you.'
 "All right, Leeana. I'll give you another chance but this is it. If you hurt me again, I'm done for good."
 "Thank you, Roma! You won't regret this, I promise!"]

 "Oh Naidelyn, that sounds terrible! I'm so sorry that happened to you! How did you find out?"
 'Well, I waited for her for over an hour and then I called her phone but she didn\'t answer so I left a voicemail asking where she was and telling her that I was going home. Then about 10 minutes later she texts me saying "Sorry, something came up last minute." Can you believe that? Something came up last minute? That\'s such a lame excuse!'
 "Yeah, that is a really lame excuse. I'm so sorry she did that to you. What are you going to do now?"
 "I don't know. I'm just going to forget about her, I guess. There are plenty of other fish in the sea."
 "That's the right attitude! You'll find someone better who will appreciate you for who you are."]

dialogue:
['Hey Izel, how are you doing today?' "I'm fine, thank you. And yourself?"
 "I'm good. Just wanted to say hi and see how you're doing."
 "I'm fine, thank you. Is there anything else you wanted to say?"
 'No, not really. I just wanted to talk to you and get to know you better.'
 "There's nothing much to know about me. I'm just a normal person."
 "Come on, there must be something interesting about you that I don't know. Tell me something about yourself that I wouldn't expect."
 'Well, I used to be a professional ballet dancer. But then I injured my ankle and had to stop dancing. That\'s why I started working at the library."'
